Oct 31 2005	No Bed 	Although a very good bargain for San Francisco, and located within walking distance to Union Square, this bare-bones hotel definitely does NOT fit the description or live up to the name of a &quot;bed and breakfast.&quot;With no lobby, the glassed-in office is a walk up a flight of stairs (or a ride on a very rickety old elevator). No sign of any common gathering area.Our room was very clean. Even the bathroom had shiny tile in the shower and the chrome was polished, the floors were clean. No signs of bugs when we turned on the lights (believe me, from the halls and the outside of this hotel, I would have expected to find bugs). But no complaints about the cleanliness of the room.Once checked in, we called the desk to inquire about breakfast. We were told that there was no place for the guests to gather and have breakfast. Rather, there would be sweet rolls and coffee outside the office in the morning. Next morning, we learned that this consisted of one box of grocery store Danish pastries and one pot of coffee. If you didn't get there early, you were out of luck.Our main complaint, however, was about the linens. The one blanket on the bed was pilled, old and stained. The bottom sheet was not fitted, and kept coming off in the night. We were not very comfortable sleeping on the mattress cover with no sheet half the night. The top sheet had a hole in it.The towels were thin and rough. The first day, one of the towels actually ripped it was so worn out. We had an extra blanket in our car and ended up bringing it up to the room rather than use the blanket provided. When we complained about no fitted bottom sheet, they did replace our bottom sheet with a bigger flat sheet and the sheet didn't come off in the night.A good bargain, but next time, we'll pay a little more and get a nicer room.	
